ACV_2_5_war&&MetadataCompleteForModules: Set the metadata-complete attribute of the deployment descriptor for the module
ACV_2_5_war&&The metadata-complete attribute defines whether the deployment descriptor for this module is complete. Set the metadata-complete attribute to "true" to merge and persist annotation-based metadata with existing XML-based deployment descriptor metedata to avoid scanning of annotation-based metadata each time the module is read. If the attribute remains "false", then the annotation-based metadata is scanned each time the module is read and can impact performance.

AdmRegContable&&MapJaspiProvider: Configure JASPI authentication.

AdmRegContable&&JASPI provider name:  
AdmRegContable&&
AdmRegContable&&MapRolesToUsers: Mapping users to roles
AdmRegContable&&Each role that is defined in the application or module must map to a user or group from the domain user registry.
AdmRegContable&&accessIds:
AdmRegContable&&	The accessIds are required only when using cross realm communication in a multi domain scenario. For all other scenarios the accessId will be determined during the application start based on the user or group name. The accessIds represent the user and group information that is used for Java Platform, Enterprise Edition authorization when using the WebSphere default authorization engine. The format for the accessIds is user:realm/uniqueUserID, group:realm/uniqueGroupID. Entering wrong information in these fields will cause authorization to fail.
AdmRegContable&&AllAuthenticatedInTrustedRealms:
AdmRegContable&&	This indicates that any valid user in the trusted realms be given the access.
AdmRegContable&&AllAuthenticated:

AdmRegContable&&Each role that is defined in the application or module must map to a user or group from the domain user registry.
AdmRegContable&&accessIds:
AdmRegContable&&	The accessIds are required only when using cross realm communication in a multi domain scenario. For all other scenarios the accessId will be determined during the application start based on the user or group name. The accessIds represent the user and group information that is used for Java Platform, Enterprise Edition authorization when using the WebSphere default authorization engine. The format for the accessIds is user:realm/uniqueUserID, group:realm/uniqueGroupID. Entering wrong information in these fields will cause authorization to fail.

AdmRegistroContableWS&&Each role that is defined in the application or module must map to a user or group from the domain user registry.
AdmRegistroContableWS&&accessIds:
AdmRegistroContableWS&&	The accessIds are required only when using cross realm communication in a multi domain scenario. For all other scenarios the accessId will be determined during the application start based on the user or group name. The accessIds represent the user and group information that is used for Java Platform, Enterprise Edition authorization when using the WebSphere default authorization engine. The format for the accessIds is user:realm/uniqueUserID, group:realm/uniqueGroupID. Entering wrong information in these fields will cause authorization to fail.

AdmRegistroContableWS85&&accessIds:
AdmRegistroContableWS85&&	The accessIds are required only when using cross realm communication in a multi domain scenario. For all other scenarios the accessId will be determined during the application start based on the user or group name. The accessIds represent the user and group information that is used for Java Platform, Enterprise Edition authorization when using the WebSphere default authorization engine. The format for the accessIds is user:realm/uniqueUserID, group:realm/uniqueGroupID. Entering wrong information in these fields will cause authorization to fail.

Ajuste&&MapRolesToUsers: Mapping users to roles
Ajuste&&Each role that is defined in the application or module must map to a user or group from the domain user registry.
Ajuste&&accessIds:
Ajuste&&	The accessIds are required only when using cross realm communication in a multi domain scenario. For all other scenarios the accessId will be determined during the application start based on the user or group name. The accessIds represent the user and group information that is used for Java Platform, Enterprise Edition authorization when using the WebSphere default authorization engine. The format for the accessIds is user:realm/uniqueUserID, group:realm/uniqueGroupID. Entering wrong information in these fields will cause authorization to fail.
Ajuste&&AllAuthenticatedInTrustedRealms:
Ajuste&&	This indicates that any valid user in the trusted realms be given the access.
Ajuste&&AllAuthenticated:
Ajuste&&	This indicates that any valid user in the current realm be given the access.

Ajuste&&MetadataCompleteForModules: Set the metadata-complete attribute of the deployment descriptor for the module
Ajuste&&The metadata-complete attribute defines whether the deployment descriptor for this module is complete. Set the metadata-complete attribute to "true" to merge and persist annotation-based metadata with existing XML-based deployment descriptor metedata to avoid scanning of annotation-based metadata each time the module is read. If the attribute remains "false", then the annotation-based metadata is scanned each time the module is read and can impact performance.

AjusteMovilWSEar&&Specify shared libraries that the application or individual modules reference. These libraries must be defined in the configuration at the appropriate scope.
AjusteMovilWSEar&&Module:  AjusteMovilWS
AjusteMovilWSEar&&URI:  AjusteMovilWS.war,WEB-INF/web.xml
AjusteMovilWSEar&&Shared Libraries:  
AjusteMovilWSEar&&
AjusteMovilWSEar&&SharedLibRelationship: Assign asset or composition unit IDs as shared libraries to the application or each module
AjusteMovilWSEar&&Specify asset or composition unit IDs as shared libraries that the application or individual modules reference. If a composition unit ID is specified, it must be part of the business level application that this enterprise application belongs to. If an asset ID is specified, a composition unit is created from the asset.
AjusteMovilWSEar&&When editing an application, only composition unit IDs can be specified as shared libraries.
AjusteMovilWSEar&&Module:  AjusteMovilWS
AjusteMovilWSEar&&URI:  AjusteMovilWS.war,WEB-INF/web.xml
AjusteMovilWSEar&&Asset or composition unit IDs:  
AjusteMovilWSEar&&Composition Unit names:  
AjusteMovilWSEar&&Match target:  Yes

AjusteMovilWSpreprod&&MapModulesToServers: Selecting servers
AjusteMovilWSpreprod&&Specify targets such as application servers or clusters of application servers where you want to install the modules that are contained in your application. Modules can be installed on the same application server or dispersed among several application servers. 
AjusteMovilWSpreprod&&Also, specify the Web servers as targets that serve as routers for requests to this application. 
AjusteMovilWSpreprod&&The plug-in configuration file (plugin-cfg.xml) for each Web server is generated, based on the applications that are routed through.
AjusteMovilWSpreprod&&Module:  AjusteMovilWS
AjusteMovilWSpreprod&&URI:  AjusteMovilWSpreprod.war,WEB-INF/web.xml
AjusteMovilWSpreprod&&Server:  WebSphere:cell=AXACellQA,cluster=cluster14_PreProd+WebSphere:cell=AXACellQA,node=apacheNode01PreProd,server=apacheInt_PreProd+WebSphere:cell=AXACellQA,node=apacheNode02PreProd,server=apacheInt_PreProd+WebSphere:cell=AXACellQA,node=apacheNode03PreProd,server=apacheInt_PreProd+WebSphere:cell=AXACellQA,node=apacheNode04PreProd,server=apacheInt_PreProd
AjusteMovilWSpreprod&&
AjusteMovilWSpreprod&&MapJaspiProvider: Configure JASPI authentication.
AjusteMovilWSpreprod&&JASPI providers offer an alternative to JAAS pluggable authentication for web modules.  By default, an application inherits the JASPI settings defined in the WebSphere Application Server global or domain security configuration and web modules inherit the application setting.  However, you can override these defaults by using wsadmin or the administrative console.
AjusteMovilWSpreprod&&Module:  AjusteMovilWSpreprod
AjusteMovilWSpreprod&&URI:  META-INF/application.xml
AjusteMovilWSpreprod&&Use JASPI:  Inherit
AjusteMovilWSpreprod&&JASPI provider name:  
AjusteMovilWSpreprod&&Module:  AjusteMovilWS
AjusteMovilWSpreprod&&URI:  AjusteMovilWSpreprod.war,WEB-INF/web.xml
AjusteMovilWSpreprod&&Use JASPI:  Inherit
AjusteMovilWSpreprod&&JASPI provider name:  
AjusteMovilWSpreprod&&
AjusteMovilWSpreprod&&MapRolesToUsers: Mapping users to roles
AjusteMovilWSpreprod&&Each role that is defined in the application or module must map to a user or group from the domain user registry.
AjusteMovilWSpreprod&&accessIds:
AjusteMovilWSpreprod&&	The accessIds are required only when using cross realm communication in a multi domain scenario. For all other scenarios the accessId will be determined during the application start based on the user or group name. The accessIds represent the user and group information that is used for Java Platform, Enterprise Edition authorization when using the WebSphere default authorization engine. The format for the accessIds is user:realm/uniqueUserID, group:realm/uniqueGroupID. Entering wrong information in these fields will cause authorization to fail.
AjusteMovilWSpreprod&&AllAuthenticatedInTrustedRealms:
AjusteMovilWSpreprod&&	This indicates that any valid user in the trusted realms be given the access.
AjusteMovilWSpreprod&&AllAuthenticated:
AjusteMovilWSpreprod&&	This indicates that any valid user in the current realm be given the access.
AjusteMovilWSpreprod&&Role:  MXAppS_AjusteMovil_SecInternalRole
AjusteMovilWSpreprod&&Everyone?:  No
AjusteMovilWSpreprod&&All authenticated?:  No
AjusteMovilWSpreprod&&Mapped users:  
AjusteMovilWSpreprod&&Mapped groups:  MXAppS_SClaims_WS_Claims|MXAppS_AjusteMovil_WSGroup
AjusteMovilWSpreprod&&All authenticated in trusted realms?:  No
AjusteMovilWSpreprod&&Mapped users access ids:  
AjusteMovilWSpreprod&&Mapped groups access ids:  group:AXARealm/CN=MXAppS_SClaims_WS_Claims,OU=Groups,OU=Usuarios,OU=AXA Mexico,DC=ASEFITEST,DC=MEX|group:AXARealm/CN=MXAppS_AjusteMovil_WSGroup,OU=Groups,OU=Usuarios,OU=AXA Mexico,DC=ASEFITEST,DC=MEX

AjusteMovilWSpreprod&&
AjusteMovilWSpreprod&&MetadataCompleteForModules: Set the metadata-complete attribute of the deployment descriptor for the module
AjusteMovilWSpreprod&&The metadata-complete attribute defines whether the deployment descriptor for this module is complete. Set the metadata-complete attribute to "true" to merge and persist annotation-based metadata with existing XML-based deployment descriptor metedata to avoid scanning of annotation-based metadata each time the module is read. If the attribute remains "false", then the annotation-based metadata is scanned each time the module is read and can impact performance. 
AjusteMovilWSpreprod&&Module:  AjusteMovilWS
AjusteMovilWSpreprod&&URI:  AjusteMovilWSpreprod.war,WEB-INF/web.xml
AjusteMovilWSpreprod&&metadata-complete attribute:  false

Ajustepreprod&&MapJaspiProvider: Configure JASPI authentication.
Ajustepreprod&&JASPI providers offer an alternative to JAAS pluggable authentication for web modules.  By default, an application inherits the JASPI settings defined in the WebSphere Application Server global or domain security configuration and web modules inherit the application setting.  However, you can override these defaults by using wsadmin or the administrative console.

Ajustepreprod&&MapRolesToUsers: Mapping users to roles
Ajustepreprod&&Each role that is defined in the application or module must map to a user or group from the domain user registry.
Ajustepreprod&&accessIds:
Ajustepreprod&&	The accessIds are required only when using cross realm communication in a multi domain scenario. For all other scenarios the accessId will be determined during the application start based on the user or group name. The accessIds represent the user and group information that is used for Java Platform, Enterprise Edition authorization when using the WebSphere default authorization engine. The format for the accessIds is user:realm/uniqueUserID, group:realm/uniqueGroupID. Entering wrong information in these fields will cause authorization to fail.
Ajustepreprod&&AllAuthenticatedInTrustedRealms:
Ajustepreprod&&	This indicates that any valid user in the trusted realms be given the access.
Ajustepreprod&&AllAuthenticated:
Ajustepreprod&&	This indicates that any valid user in the current realm be given the access.
Ajustepreprod&&Role:  MXAppS_Ajuste_NormatividadRole

Ajustepreprod&&MetadataCompleteForModules: Set the metadata-complete attribute of the deployment descriptor for the module
Ajustepreprod&&The metadata-complete attribute defines whether the deployment descriptor for this module is complete. Set the metadata-complete attribute to "true" to merge and persist annotation-based metadata with existing XML-based deployment descriptor metedata to avoid scanning of annotation-based metadata each time the module is read. If the attribute remains "false", then the annotation-based metadata is scanned each time the module is read and can impact performance. 
Ajustepreprod&&Module:  Monitores-View
Ajustepreprod&&URI:  Ajustepreprod.war,WEB-INF/web.xml
Ajustepreprod&&metadata-complete attribute:  false

AutosFlotilla&&MetadataCompleteForModules: Set the metadata-complete attribute of the deployment descriptor for the module
AutosFlotilla&&The metadata-complete attribute defines whether the deployment descriptor for this module is complete. Set the metadata-complete attribute to "true" to merge and persist annotation-based metadata with existing XML-based deployment descriptor metedata to avoid scanning of annotation-based metadata each time the module is read. If the attribute remains "false", then the annotation-based metadata is scanned each time the module is read and can impact performance.

BPMPP&&
BPMPP&&MapRolesToUsers: Mapping users to roles
BPMPP&&Each role that is defined in the application or module must map to a user or group from the domain user registry.
BPMPP&&accessIds:
BPMPP&&	The accessIds are required only when using cross realm communication in a multi domain scenario. For all other scenarios the accessId will be determined during the application start based on the user or group name. The accessIds represent the user and group information that is used for Java Platform, Enterprise Edition authorization when using the WebSphere default authorization engine. The format for the accessIds is user:realm/uniqueUserID, group:realm/uniqueGroupID. Entering wrong information in these fields will cause authorization to fail.
BPMPP&&AllAuthenticatedInTrustedRealms:
BPMPP&&	This indicates that any valid user in the trusted realms be given the access.
BPMPP&&AllAuthenticated:
BPMPP&&	This indicates that any valid user in the current realm be given the access.
BPMPP&&Role:  UserPPWebBPMRole
BPMPP&&Everyone?:  No
BPMPP&&All authenticated?:  Yes
BPMPP&&Mapped users:  
BPMPP&&Mapped groups:  
BPMPP&&All authenticated in trusted realms?:  No
BPMPP&&Mapped users access ids:  
BPMPP&&Mapped groups access ids:

BolsasCupos&&
BolsasCupos&&MetadataCompleteForModules: Set the metadata-complete attribute of the deployment descriptor for the module
BolsasCupos&&The metadata-complete attribute defines whether the deployment descriptor for this module is complete. Set the metadata-complete attribute to "true" to merge and persist annotation-based metadata with existing XML-based deployment descriptor metedata to avoid scanning of annotation-based metadata each time the module is read. If the attribute remains "false", then the annotation-based metadata is scanned each time the module is read and can impact performance. 
BolsasCupos&&Module:  BolsasCupos.war
BolsasCupos&&URI:  BolsasCupos.war,WEB-INF/web.xml
BolsasCupos&&metadata-complete attribute:  false

However, you can override these defaults by using wsadmin or the administrative console.

BolsasCuposBatch&&MapRolesToUsers: Mapping users to roles
BolsasCuposBatch&&Each role that is defined in the application or module must map to a user or group from the domain user registry.
BolsasCuposBatch&&accessIds:
BolsasCuposBatch&&	The accessIds are required only when using cross realm communication in a multi domain scenario. For all other scenarios the accessId will be determined during the application start based on the user or group name. The accessIds represent the user and group information that is used for Java Platform, Enterprise Edition authorization when using the WebSphere default authorization engine. The format for the accessIds is user:realm/uniqueUserID, group:realm/uniqueGroupID. Entering wrong information in these fields will cause authorization to fail.
BolsasCuposBatch&&AllAuthenticatedInTrustedRealms:
BolsasCuposBatch&&	This indicates that any valid user in the trusted realms be given the access.
BolsasCuposBatch&&AllAuthenticated:
BolsasCuposBatch&&	This indicates that any valid user in the current realm be given the access.

CatalogosAutosWS_2&&MapRolesToUsers: Mapping users to roles
CatalogosAutosWS_2&&Each role that is defined in the application or module must map to a user or group from the domain user registry.
CatalogosAutosWS_2&&accessIds:
CatalogosAutosWS_2&&	The accessIds are required only when using cross realm communication in a multi domain scenario. For all other scenarios the accessId will be determined during the application start based on the user or group name. The accessIds represent the user and group information that is used for Java Platform, Enterprise Edition authorization when using the WebSphere default authorization engine. The format for the accessIds is user:realm/uniqueUserID, group:realm/uniqueGroupID. Entering wrong information in these fields will cause authorization to fail.
CatalogosAutosWS_2&&AllAuthenticatedInTrustedRealms:
CatalogosAutosWS_2&&	This indicates that any valid user in the trusted realms be given the access.
CatalogosAutosWS_2&&AllAuthenticated:
CatalogosAutosWS_2&&	This indicates that any valid user in the current realm be given the access.
CatalogosAutosWS_2&&Role:  MXAppS_EMA_WSEmisionSecRole
CatalogosAutosWS_2&&Everyone?:  No
CatalogosAutosWS_2&&All authenticated?:  No
CatalogosAutosWS_2&&Mapped users:  
CatalogosAutosWS_2&&Mapped groups:  MXAppS_EMA_WSEmisionSecRole
CatalogosAutosWS_2&&All authenticated in trusted realms?:  No
CatalogosAutosWS_2&&Mapped users access ids:  
CatalogosAutosWS_2&&Mapped groups access ids:  group:AXARealm/CN=MXAppS_EMA_WSEmisionSecRole,OU=Groups,OU=Usuarios,OU=AXA Mexico,DC=ASEFITEST,DC=MEX

CentroNotificacionesServices_war&&The metadata-complete attribute defines whether the deployment descriptor for this module is complete. If the attribute remains "false", then the annotation-based metadata is scanned each time the module is read and can impact performance.

ClaimAutos&&MapRolesToUsers: Mapping users to roles
ClaimAutos&&Each role that is defined in the application or module must map to a user or group from the domain user registry.
ClaimAutos&&accessIds:
ClaimAutos&&	The accessIds are required only when using cross realm communication in a multi domain scenario. For all other scenarios the accessId will be determined during the application start based on the user or group name. The accessIds represent the user and group information that is used for Java Platform, Enterprise Edition authorization when using the WebSphere default authorization engine. The format for the accessIds is user:realm/uniqueUserID, group:realm/uniqueGroupID. Entering wrong information in these fields will cause authorization to fail.
ClaimAutos&&AllAuthenticatedInTrustedRealms:
ClaimAutos&&	This indicates that any valid user in the trusted realms be given the access.
ClaimAutos&&AllAuthenticated:
ClaimAutos&&	This indicates that any valid user in the current realm be given the access.
ClaimAutos&&Role:  MXAppS_SWORKSITE_WSClaim
ClaimAutos&&Everyone?:  No
ClaimAutos&&All authenticated?:  No
ClaimAutos&&Mapped users:  
ClaimAutos&&Mapped groups:  MXAppS_SWORKSITE_WSClaim
ClaimAutos&&All authenticated in trusted realms?:  No

ClaimAutos&&Mapped groups access ids:  group:AXARealm/CN=MXAppS_SWORKSITE_WSClaim,OU=Groups,OU=Usuarios,OU=AXA Mexico,DC=ASEFITEST,DC=MEX

ClaimAutos&&JASPI providers offer an alternative to JAAS pluggable authentication for web modules. However, you can override these defaults by using wsadmin or the administrative console.

ClaimAutos&&
ClaimAutos&&MapRolesToUsers: Mapping users to roles
ClaimAutos&&Each role that is defined in the application or module must map to a user or group from the domain user registry.
ClaimAutos&&accessIds:
ClaimAutos&&	The accessIds are required only when using cross realm communication in a multi domain scenario. For all other scenarios the accessId will be determined during the application start based on the user or group name. The accessIds represent the user and group information that is used for Java Platform, Enterprise Edition authorization when using the WebSphere default authorization engine. The format for the accessIds is user:realm/uniqueUserID, group:realm/uniqueGroupID. Entering wrong information in these fields will cause authorization to fail.
ClaimAutos&&AllAuthenticatedInTrustedRealms:
ClaimAutos&&	This indicates that any valid user in the trusted realms be given the access.
ClaimAutos&&AllAuthenticated:
ClaimAutos&&	This indicates that any valid user in the current realm be given the access.
ClaimAutos&&Role:  MXAppS_SWORKSITE_WSClaim
ClaimAutos&&Everyone?:  No
ClaimAutos&&All authenticated?:  No
ClaimAutos&&Mapped users:  
ClaimAutos&&Mapped groups:  MXAppS_SWORKSITE_WSClaim
ClaimAutos&&All authenticated in trusted realms?:  No
ClaimAutos&&Mapped users access ids:  
ClaimAutos&&Mapped groups access ids:  group:AXARealm/CN=MXAppS_SWORKSITE_WSClaim,OU=Groups,OU=Usuarios,OU=AXA Mexico,DC=ASEFITEST,DC=MEX

ClaimAutos&&MetadataCompleteForModules: Set the metadata-complete attribute of the deployment descriptor for the module
ClaimAutos&&The metadata-complete attribute defines whether the deployment descriptor for this module is complete. Set the metadata-complete attribute to "true" to merge and persist annotation-based metadata with existing XML-based deployment descriptor metedata to avoid scanning of annotation-based metadata each time the module is read. If the attribute remains "false", then the annotation-based metadata is scanned each time the module is read and can impact performance.

ConsultaAgentes&&MapJaspiProvider: Configure JASPI authentication.
ConsultaAgentes&&JASPI providers offer an alternative to JAAS pluggable authentication for web modules.  By default, an application inherits the JASPI settings defined in the WebSphere Application Server global or domain security configuration and web modules inherit the application setting.  However, you can override these defaults by using wsadmin or the administrative console.

ConsultaAgentes&&MapRolesToUsers: Mapping users to roles
ConsultaAgentes&&Each role that is defined in the application or module must map to a user or group from the domain user registry.
ConsultaAgentes&&accessIds:
ConsultaAgentes&&	The accessIds are required only when using cross realm communication in a multi domain scenario. For all other scenarios the accessId will be determined during the application start based on the user or group name. The accessIds represent the user and group information that is used for Java Platform, Enterprise Edition authorization when using the WebSphere default authorization engine. The format for the accessIds is user:realm/uniqueUserID, group:realm/uniqueGroupID. Entering wrong information in these fields will cause authorization to fail.
ConsultaAgentes&&AllAuthenticatedInTrustedRealms:
ConsultaAgentes&&	This indicates that any valid user in the trusted realms be given the access.
ConsultaAgentes&&AllAuthenticated:
ConsultaAgentes&&	This indicates that any valid user in the current realm be given the access.

ControlCitas_war&&
ControlCitas_war&&MapRolesToUsers: Mapping users to roles
ControlCitas_war&&Each role that is defined in the application or module must map to a user or group from the domain user registry.
ControlCitas_war&&accessIds:
ControlCitas_war&&	The accessIds are required only when using cross realm communication in a multi domain scenario. For all other scenarios the accessId will be determined during the application start based on the user or group name. The accessIds represent the user and group information that is used for Java Platform, Enterprise Edition authorization when using the WebSphere default authorization engine. The format for the accessIds is user:realm/uniqueUserID, group:realm/uniqueGroupID. Entering wrong information in these fields will cause authorization to fail.
ControlCitas_war&&AllAuthenticatedInTrustedRealms:
ControlCitas_war&&	This indicates that any valid user in the trusted realms be given the access.
ControlCitas_war&&AllAuthenticated:
ControlCitas_war&&	This indicates that any valid user in the current realm be given the access.
ControlCitas_war&&Role:  AgentesWS_consulta
ControlCitas_war&&Everyone?:  No
ControlCitas_war&&All authenticated?:  No
ControlCitas_war&&Mapped users:  
ControlCitas_war&&Mapped groups:  MXAppS_AGENTESWS_CONSULTA
ControlCitas_war&&All authenticated in trusted realms?:  No
ControlCitas_war&&Mapped users access ids:  
ControlCitas_war&&Mapped groups access ids:  group:AXARealm/CN=MXAppS_AGENTESWS_CONSULTA,OU=Groups,OU=Usuarios,OU=AXA Mexico,DC=ASEFITEST,DC=MEX

CotizadorAutosRC-portlet_war&&MetadataCompleteForModules: Set the metadata-complete attribute of the deployment descriptor for the module
CotizadorAutosRC-portlet_war&&The metadata-complete attribute defines whether the deployment descriptor for this module is complete. Set the metadata-complete attribute to "true" to merge and persist annotation-based metadata with existing XML-based deployment descriptor metedata to avoid scanning of annotation-based metadata each time the module is read. If the attribute remains "false", then the annotation-based metadata is scanned each time the module is read and can impact performance.

CotizadorAutosVPIBancs-portlet_war&&MetadataCompleteForModules: Set the metadata-complete attribute of the deployment descriptor for the module
CotizadorAutosVPIBancs-portlet_war&&The metadata-complete attribute defines whether the deployment descriptor for this module is complete. Set the metadata-complete attribute to "true" to merge and persist annotation-based metadata with existing XML-based deployment descriptor metedata to avoid scanning of annotation-based metadata each time the module is read. If the attribute remains "false", then the annotation-based metadata is scanned each time the module is read and can impact performance.

CotizadorFlxPlsPkg-portlet_war&&MetadataCompleteForModules: Set the metadata-complete attribute of the deployment descriptor for the module
CotizadorFlxPlsPkg-portlet_war&&The metadata-complete attribute defines whether the deployment descriptor for this module is complete. Set the metadata-complete attribute to "true" to merge and persist annotation-based metadata with existing XML-based deployment descriptor metedata to avoid scanning of annotation-based metadata each time the module is read. If the attribute remains "false", then the annotation-based metadata is scanned each time the module is read and can impact performance.

CotizadorPBE&&accessIds:
CotizadorPBE&&	The accessIds are required only when using cross realm communication in a multi domain scenario. For all other scenarios the accessId will be determined during the application start based on the user or group name. The accessIds represent the user and group information that is used for Java Platform, Enterprise Edition authorization when using the WebSphere default authorization engine. The format for the accessIds is user:realm/uniqueUserID, group:realm/uniqueGroupID. Entering wrong information in these fields will cause authorization to fail.
CotizadorPBE&&AllAuthenticatedInTrustedRealms:
CotizadorPBE&&	This indicates that any valid user in the trusted realms be given the access.
CotizadorPBE&&AllAuthenticated:
CotizadorPBE&&	This indicates that any valid user in the current realm be given the access.

CotizadorPBE&&BindJndiForEJBNonMessageBinding: Binding enterprise Bean to JNDI names
CotizadorPBE&&Each non-message-driven enterprise bean in your application or module must be bound to a Java Naming and Directory Interface (JNDI) name. For beans in a pre-EJB 3.0 module, you have to use JNDI name for the bean to provide the binding. For beans in a EJB 3.0 module, you can optionally provide binding through JNDI name for the bean or local/remote home JNDI names. If JNDI name for the bean is specified, you cannot specify binding for its local/remote home and any business interface. If no JNDI name is specified for beans in a EJB 3.0 module, runtime will provide a container default.

Cotizador_Flotillas_Pymes&&MapRolesToUsers: Mapping users to roles
Cotizador_Flotillas_Pymes&&Each role that is defined in the application or module must map to a user or group from the domain user registry.
Cotizador_Flotillas_Pymes&&accessIds:
Cotizador_Flotillas_Pymes&&	The accessIds are required only when using cross realm communication in a multi domain scenario. For all other scenarios the accessId will be determined during the application start based on the user or group name. The accessIds represent the user and group information that is used for Java Platform, Enterprise Edition authorization when using the WebSphere default authorization engine. The format for the accessIds is user:realm/uniqueUserID, group:realm/uniqueGroupID. Entering wrong information in these fields will cause authorization to fail.
Cotizador_Flotillas_Pymes&&AllAuthenticatedInTrustedRealms:
Cotizador_Flotillas_Pymes&&	This indicates that any valid user in the trusted realms be given the access.
Cotizador_Flotillas_Pymes&&AllAuthenticated:
Cotizador_Flotillas_Pymes&&	This indicates that any valid user in the current realm be given the access.

If the attribute remains "false", then the annotation-based metadata is scanned each time the module is read and can impact performance.

EmisionPolizasWS&&MapRolesToUsers: Mapping users to roles
EmisionPolizasWS&&Each role that is defined in the application or module must map to a user or group from the domain user registry.
EmisionPolizasWS&&accessIds:
EmisionPolizasWS&&	The accessIds are required only when using cross realm communication in a multi domain scenario. For all other scenarios the accessId will be determined during the application start based on the user or group name. The accessIds represent the user and group information that is used for Java Platform, Enterprise Edition authorization when using the WebSphere default authorization engine. The format for the accessIds is user:realm/uniqueUserID, group:realm/uniqueGroupID. Entering wrong information in these fields will cause authorization to fail.
EmisionPolizasWS&&AllAuthenticatedInTrustedRealms:
EmisionPolizasWS&&	This indicates that any valid user in the trusted realms be given the access.
EmisionPolizasWS&&AllAuthenticated:
EmisionPolizasWS&&	This indicates that any valid user in the current realm be given the access.

EmisionPolizasWS&&All authenticated?:  Yes
EmisionPolizasWS&&Mapped users:

EnvioCorreosAdmin_war&&accessIds:
EnvioCorreosAdmin_war&&	The accessIds are required only when using cross realm communication in a multi domain scenario. For all other scenarios the accessId will be determined during the application start based on the user or group name. The accessIds represent the user and group information that is used for Java Platform, Enterprise Edition authorization when using the WebSphere default authorization engine. The format for the accessIds is user:realm/uniqueUserID, group:realm/uniqueGroupID. Entering wrong information in these fields will cause authorization to fail.

EnvioCorreosAdmin_war&&MetadataCompleteForModules: Set the metadata-complete attribute of the deployment descriptor for the module
EnvioCorreosAdmin_war&&The metadata-complete attribute defines whether the deployment descriptor for this module is complete. Set the metadata-complete attribute to "true" to merge and persist annotation-based metadata with existing XML-based deployment descriptor metedata to avoid scanning of annotation-based metadata each time the module is read. If the attribute remains "false", then the annotation-based metadata is scanned each time the module is read and can impact performance.

ExpedienteElectronicoApp_war&&MetadataCompleteForModules: Set the metadata-complete attribute of the deployment descriptor for the module
ExpedienteElectronicoApp_war&&The metadata-complete attribute defines whether the deployment descriptor for this module is complete. Set the metadata-complete attribute to "true" to merge and persist annotation-based metadata with existing XML-based deployment descriptor metedata to avoid scanning of annotation-based metadata each time the module is read. If the attribute remains "false", then the annotation-based metadata is scanned each time the module is read and can impact performance.

ExpedienteElectronico_war&&accessIds:
ExpedienteElectronico_war&&	The accessIds are required only when using cross realm communication in a multi domain scenario. For all other scenarios the accessId will be determined during the application start based on the user or group name. The accessIds represent the user and group information that is used for Java Platform, Enterprise Edition authorization when using the WebSphere default authorization engine. The format for the accessIds is user:realm/uniqueUserID, group:realm/uniqueGroupID. Entering wrong information in these fields will cause authorization to fail.
ExpedienteElectronico_war&&AllAuthenticatedInTrustedRealms:
ExpedienteElectronico_war&&	This indicates that any valid user in the trusted realms be given the access.
ExpedienteElectronico_war&&AllAuthenticated:
ExpedienteElectronico_war&&	This indicates that any valid user in the current realm be given the access.

FicheroVehiculosBatch&&accessIds:
FicheroVehiculosBatch&&	The accessIds are required only when using cross realm communication in a multi domain scenario. For all other scenarios the accessId will be determined during the application start based on the user or group name. The accessIds represent the user and group information that is used for Java Platform, Enterprise Edition authorization when using the WebSphere default authorization engine. The format for the accessIds is user:realm/uniqueUserID, group:realm/uniqueGroupID. Entering wrong information in these fields will cause authorization to fail.
FicheroVehiculosBatch&&AllAuthenticatedInTrustedRealms:
FicheroVehiculosBatch&&	This indicates that any valid user in the trusted realms be given the access.

FicheroVehiculosBatch&&MetadataCompleteForModules: Set the metadata-complete attribute of the deployment descriptor for the module
FicheroVehiculosBatch&&The metadata-complete attribute defines whether the deployment descriptor for this module is complete. Set the metadata-complete attribute to "true" to merge and persist annotation-based metadata with existing XML-based deployment descriptor metedata to avoid scanning of annotation-based metadata each time the module is read. If the attribute remains "false", then the annotation-based metadata is scanned each time the module is read and can impact performance.

FlotillasPymesWS_2&&MapRolesToUsers: Mapping users to roles
FlotillasPymesWS_2&&Each role that is defined in the application or module must map to a user or group from the domain user registry.
FlotillasPymesWS_2&&accessIds:
FlotillasPymesWS_2&&	The accessIds are required only when using cross realm communication in a multi domain scenario. For all other scenarios the accessId will be determined during the application start based on the user or group name. The accessIds represent the user and group information that is used for Java Platform, Enterprise Edition authorization when using the WebSphere default authorization engine. The format for the accessIds is user:realm/uniqueUserID, group:realm/uniqueGroupID. Entering wrong information in these fields will cause authorization to fail.
FlotillasPymesWS_2&&AllAuthenticatedInTrustedRealms:
FlotillasPymesWS_2&&	This indicates that any valid user in the trusted realms be given the access.
FlotillasPymesWS_2&&AllAuthenticated:
FlotillasPymesWS_2&&	This indicates that any valid user in the current realm be given the access.

If the attribute remains "false", then the annotation-based metadata is scanned each time the module is read and can impact performance.

GeocodificaMapasDanos_war&&The metadata-complete attribute defines whether the deployment descriptor for this module is complete. Set the metadata-complete attribute to "true" to merge and persist annotation-based metadata with existing XML-based deployment descriptor metedata to avoid scanning of annotation-based metadata each time the module is read. If the attribute remains "false", then the annotation-based metadata is scanned each time the module is read and can impact performance.

Ingresos&&The plug-in configuration file (plugin-cfg.xml) for each Web server is generated, based on the applications that are routed through.
Ingresos&&Module:  Ingresos

Ingresos&&
Ingresos&&MapJaspiProvider: Configure JASPI authentication.
Ingresos&&JASPI providers offer an alternative to JAAS pluggable authentication for web modules.  By default, an application inherits the JASPI settings defined in the WebSphere Application Server global or domain security configuration and web modules inherit the application setting.  However, you can override these defaults by using wsadmin or the administrative console.
Ingresos&&Module:  Ingresos
Ingresos&&URI:  META-INF/application.xml
Ingresos&&Use JASPI:  Inherit
Ingresos&&JASPI provider name:

Ingresos&&Use JASPI:  Inherit
Ingresos&&JASPI provider name:  
Ingresos&&
Ingresos&&MapRolesToUsers: Mapping users to roles
Ingresos&&Each role that is defined in the application or module must map to a user or group from the domain user registry.
Ingresos&&accessIds:
Ingresos&&	The accessIds are required only when using cross realm communication in a multi domain scenario. For all other scenarios the accessId will be determined during the application start based on the user or group name. The accessIds represent the user and group information that is used for Java Platform, Enterprise Edition authorization when using the WebSphere default authorization engine. The format for the accessIds is user:realm/uniqueUserID, group:realm/uniqueGroupID. Entering wrong information in these fields will cause authorization to fail.
Ingresos&&AllAuthenticatedInTrustedRealms:
Ingresos&&	This indicates that any valid user in the trusted realms be given the access.
Ingresos&&AllAuthenticated:
Ingresos&&	This indicates that any valid user in the current realm be given the access.
Ingresos&&Role:  MXAppS_SClaims_WS_Claims
Ingresos&&Everyone?:  No
Ingresos&&All authenticated?:  No
Ingresos&&Mapped users:  
Ingresos&&Mapped groups:  MXAppS_SClaims_WS_Claims
Ingresos&&All authenticated in trusted realms?:  No
Ingresos&&Mapped users access ids:  
Ingresos&&Mapped groups access ids:  group:AXARealm/CN=MXAppS_SClaims_WS_Claims,OU=Groups,OU=Usuarios,OU=AXA Mexico,DC=ASEFITEST,DC=MEX

Ingresos&&SharedLibRelationship: Assign asset or composition unit IDs as shared libraries to the application or each module
Ingresos&&Specify asset or composition unit IDs as shared libraries that the application or individual modules reference. If a composition unit ID is specified, it must be part of the business level application that this enterprise application belongs to. If an asset ID is specified, a composition unit is created from the asset.
Ingresos&&When editing an application, only composition unit IDs can be specified as shared libraries.

InterfazBanamex&&JASPI providers offer an alternative to JAAS pluggable authentication for web modules.  By default, an application inherits the JASPI settings defined in the WebSphere Application Server global or domain security configuration and web modules inherit the application setting.  However, you can override these defaults by using wsadmin or the administrative console.

InterfazBanamex&&
InterfazBanamex&&MapRolesToUsers: Mapping users to roles
InterfazBanamex&&Each role that is defined in the application or module must map to a user or group from the domain user registry.
InterfazBanamex&&accessIds:
InterfazBanamex&&	The accessIds are required only when using cross realm communication in a multi domain scenario. For all other scenarios the accessId will be determined during the application start based on the user or group name. The accessIds represent the user and group information that is used for Java Platform, Enterprise Edition authorization when using the WebSphere default authorization engine. The format for the accessIds is user:realm/uniqueUserID, group:realm/uniqueGroupID. Entering wrong information in these fields will cause authorization to fail.
InterfazBanamex&&AllAuthenticatedInTrustedRealms:
InterfazBanamex&&	This indicates that any valid user in the trusted realms be given the access.
InterfazBanamex&&AllAuthenticated:
InterfazBanamex&&	This indicates that any valid user in the current realm be given the access.

LR_AXAMX_BuscadorCondicionesGenerales_war&&
LR_AXAMX_BuscadorCondicionesGenerales_war&&MetadataCompleteForModules: Set the metadata-complete attribute of the deployment descriptor for the module
LR_AXAMX_BuscadorCondicionesGenerales_war&&The metadata-complete attribute defines whether the deployment descriptor for this module is complete. Set the metadata-complete attribute to "true" to merge and persist annotation-based metadata with existing XML-based deployment descriptor metedata to avoid scanning of annotation-based metadata each time the module is read. If the attribute remains "false", then the annotation-based metadata is scanned each time the module is read and can impact performance.

LR_AXAMX_Encuestas-portlet&&MapModulesToServers: Selecting servers
LR_AXAMX_Encuestas-portlet&&Specify targets such as application servers or clusters of application servers where you want to install the modules that are contained in your application. Modules can be installed on the same application server or dispersed among several application servers. 
LR_AXAMX_Encuestas-portlet&&Also, specify the Web servers as targets that serve as routers for requests to this application. 
LR_AXAMX_Encuestas-portlet&&The plug-in configuration file (plugin-cfg.xml) for each Web server is generated, based on the applications that are routed through.

LR_AXAMX_Encuestas-portlet&&MapJaspiProvider: Configure JASPI authentication.
LR_AXAMX_Encuestas-portlet&&JASPI providers offer an alternative to JAAS pluggable authentication for web modules.  By default, an application inherits the JASPI settings defined in the WebSphere Application Server global or domain security configuration and web modules inherit the application setting.  However, you can override these defaults by using wsadmin or the administrative console.

LR_AXA_APP_ESCOLAR-portlet_war&&MetadataCompleteForModules: Set the metadata-complete attribute of the deployment descriptor for the module
LR_AXA_APP_ESCOLAR-portlet_war&&The metadata-complete attribute defines whether the deployment descriptor for this module is complete. Set the metadata-complete attribute to "true" to merge and persist annotation-based metadata with existing XML-based deployment descriptor metedata to avoid scanning of annotation-based metadata each time the module is read. If the attribute remains "false", then the annotation-based metadata is scanned each time the module is read and can impact performance.

If an asset ID is specified, a composition unit is created from the asset.

LR_AXA_Agentes_war&&
LR_AXA_Agentes_war&&MetadataCompleteForModules: Set the metadata-complete attribute of the deployment descriptor for the module
LR_AXA_Agentes_war&&The metadata-complete attribute defines whether the deployment descriptor for this module is complete. Set the metadata-complete attribute to "true" to merge and persist annotation-based metadata with existing XML-based deployment descriptor metedata to avoid scanning of annotation-based metadata each time the module is read. If the attribute remains "false", then the annotation-based metadata is scanned each time the module is read and can impact performance.

LR_AXA_Agentes_war&&Specify runtime components that should be added to or removed from the default runtime components that are needed to run this application.  This step is for advanced users and should only be used in those cases when all the runtime components needed for the application cannot be obtained by inspecting the application.

LR_AXA_Boletines_war&&MapModulesToServers: Selecting servers
LR_AXA_Boletines_war&&Specify targets such as application servers or clusters of application servers where you want to install the modules that are contained in your application. Modules can be installed on the same application server or dispersed among several application servers. 
LR_AXA_Boletines_war&&Also, specify the Web servers as targets that serve as routers for requests to this application. 
LR_AXA_Boletines_war&&The plug-in configuration file (plugin-cfg.xml) for each Web server is generated, based on the applications that are routed through.

LR_AXA_COTIZADOR_AUTOS-VPI_war&&MapModulesToServers: Selecting servers
LR_AXA_COTIZADOR_AUTOS-VPI_war&&Specify targets such as application servers or clusters of application servers where you want to install the modules that are contained in your application. Modules can be installed on the same application server or dispersed among several application servers. 
LR_AXA_COTIZADOR_AUTOS-VPI_war&&Also, specify the Web servers as targets that serve as routers for requests to this application. 
LR_AXA_COTIZADOR_AUTOS-VPI_war&&The plug-in configuration file (plugin-cfg.xml) for each Web server is generated, based on the applications that are routed through.

LR_AXA_COTIZADOR_AUTOS-VPI_war&&MapJaspiProvider: Configure JASPI authentication.
LR_AXA_COTIZADOR_AUTOS-VPI_war&&JASPI providers offer an alternative to JAAS pluggable authentication for web modules.  By default, an application inherits the JASPI settings defined in the WebSphere Application Server global or domain security configuration and web modules inherit the application setting.  However, you can override these defaults by using wsadmin or the administrative console.

LR_AXA_COTIZADOR_AUTOS-VPI_war&&Specify asset or composition unit IDs as shared libraries that the application or individual modules reference. If a composition unit ID is specified, it must be part of the business level application that this enterprise application belongs to. If an asset ID is specified, a composition unit is created from the asset.
LR_AXA_COTIZADOR_AUTOS-VPI_war&&When editing an application, only composition unit IDs can be specified as shared libraries.

LR_AXA_COTIZADOR_AUTOS-VPI_war&&MetadataCompleteForModules: Set the metadata-complete attribute of the deployment descriptor for the module
LR_AXA_COTIZADOR_AUTOS-VPI_war&&The metadata-complete attribute defines whether the deployment descriptor for this module is complete. Set the metadata-complete attribute to "true" to merge and persist annotation-based metadata with existing XML-based deployment descriptor metedata to avoid scanning of annotation-based metadata each time the module is read. If the attribute remains "false", then the annotation-based metadata is scanned each time the module is read and can impact performance.

LR_AXA_Clientes360_war&&MetadataCompleteForModules: Set the metadata-complete attribute of the deployment descriptor for the module
LR_AXA_Clientes360_war&&The metadata-complete attribute defines whether the deployment descriptor for this module is complete. Set the metadata-complete attribute to "true" to merge and persist annotation-based metadata with existing XML-based deployment descriptor metedata to avoid scanning of annotation-based metadata each time the module is read. If the attribute remains "false", then the annotation-based metadata is scanned each time the module is read and can impact performance.

LR_AXA_Dashboard_war&&MetadataCompleteForModules: Set the metadata-complete attribute of the deployment descriptor for the module
LR_AXA_Dashboard_war&&The metadata-complete attribute defines whether the deployment descriptor for this module is complete. Set the metadata-complete attribute to "true" to merge and persist annotation-based metadata with existing XML-based deployment descriptor metedata to avoid scanning of annotation-based metadata each time the module is read. If the attribute remains "false", then the annotation-based metadata is scanned each time the module is read and can impact performance.

LR_AXA_Notifications_war&&
LR_AXA_Notifications_war&&SharedLibRelationship: Assign asset or composition unit IDs as shared libraries to the application or each module
LR_AXA_Notifications_war&&Specify asset or composition unit IDs as shared libraries that the application or individual modules reference. If a composition unit ID is specified, it must be part of the business level application that this enterprise application belongs to. If an asset ID is specified, a composition unit is created from the asset.
LR_AXA_Notifications_war&&When editing an application, only composition unit IDs can be specified as shared libraries.

LR_AXA_Notifications_war&&
LR_AXA_Notifications_war&&MetadataCompleteForModules: Set the metadata-complete attribute of the deployment descriptor for the module
LR_AXA_Notifications_war&&The metadata-complete attribute defines whether the deployment descriptor for this module is complete. Set the metadata-complete attribute to "true" to merge and persist annotation-based metadata with existing XML-based deployment descriptor metedata to avoid scanning of annotation-based metadata each time the module is read. If the attribute remains "false", then the annotation-based metadata is scanned each time the module is read and can impact performance.

LR_AXA_Notifications_war&&URI:  LR_AXA_Notifications.war,WEB-INF/web.xml

LR_AXA_Notifications_war&&Specify runtime components that should be added to or removed from the default runtime components that are needed to run this application.  This step is for advanced users and should only be used in those cases when all the runtime components needed for the application cannot be obtained by inspecting the application.

LR_AXA_PERFILADOR_VIDA_war&&MapModulesToServers: Selecting servers
LR_AXA_PERFILADOR_VIDA_war&&Specify targets such as application servers or clusters of application servers where you want to install the modules that are contained in your application. Modules can be installed on the same application server or dispersed among several application servers. 
LR_AXA_PERFILADOR_VIDA_war&&Also, specify the Web servers as targets that serve as routers for requests to this application. 
LR_AXA_PERFILADOR_VIDA_war&&The plug-in configuration file (plugin-cfg.xml) for each Web server is generated, based on the applications that are routed through.

LR_AXA_PERFILADOR_VIDA_war&&MapJaspiProvider: Configure JASPI authentication.
LR_AXA_PERFILADOR_VIDA_war&&JASPI providers offer an alternative to JAAS pluggable authentication for web modules.  By default, an application inherits the JASPI settings defined in the WebSphere Application Server global or domain security configuration and web modules inherit the application setting.  However, you can override these defaults by using wsadmin or the administrative console.

LR_AXA_Tools_war&&
LR_AXA_Tools_war&&MetadataCompleteForModules: Set the metadata-complete attribute of the deployment descriptor for the module
LR_AXA_Tools_war&&The metadata-complete attribute defines whether the deployment descriptor for this module is complete. Set the metadata-complete attribute to "true" to merge and persist annotation-based metadata with existing XML-based deployment descriptor metedata to avoid scanning of annotation-based metadata each time the module is read. If the attribute remains "false", then the annotation-based metadata is scanned each time the module is read and can impact performance.

LR_AXA_Tools_war&&URI:  LR_AXA_Tools.war,WEB-INF/web.xml

LR_MYAXA_Chat_war&&The metadata-complete attribute defines whether the deployment descriptor for this module is complete. Set the metadata-complete attribute to "true" to merge and persist annotation-based metadata with existing XML-based deployment descriptor metedata to avoid scanning of annotation-based metadata each time the module is read. If the attribute remains "false", then the annotation-based metadata is scanned each time the module is read and can impact performance.

LR_MYAXA_MisPolizas_war&&MetadataCompleteForModules: Set the metadata-complete attribute of the deployment descriptor for the module
LR_MYAXA_MisPolizas_war&&The metadata-complete attribute defines whether the deployment descriptor for this module is complete. Set the metadata-complete attribute to "true" to merge and persist annotation-based metadata with existing XML-based deployment descriptor metedata to avoid scanning of annotation-based metadata each time the module is read. If the attribute remains "false", then the annotation-based metadata is scanned each time the module is read and can impact performance.

LR_MYAXA_PublicApps_war&&JASPI providers offer an alternative to JAAS pluggable authentication for web modules.  By default, an application inherits the JASPI settings defined in the WebSphere Application Server global or domain security configuration and web modules inherit the application setting.  However, you can override these defaults by using wsadmin or the administrative console.

LR_MYAXA_PublicApps_war&&SharedLibRelationship: Assign asset or composition unit IDs as shared libraries to the application or each module
LR_MYAXA_PublicApps_war&&Specify asset or composition unit IDs as shared libraries that the application or individual modules reference. If a composition unit ID is specified, it must be part of the business level application that this enterprise application belongs to. If an asset ID is specified, a composition unit is created from the asset.
LR_MYAXA_PublicApps_war&&When editing an application, only composition unit IDs can be specified as shared libraries.

LR_MYAXA_PublicApps_war&&
LR_MYAXA_PublicApps_war&&MetadataCompleteForModules: Set the metadata-complete attribute of the deployment descriptor for the module
LR_MYAXA_PublicApps_war&&The metadata-complete attribute defines whether the deployment descriptor for this module is complete. Set the metadata-complete attribute to "true" to merge and persist annotation-based metadata with existing XML-based deployment descriptor metedata to avoid scanning of annotation-based metadata each time the module is read. If the attribute remains "false", then the annotation-based metadata is scanned each time the module is read and can impact performance.

LR_MYAXA_PublicApps_war&&URI:  LR_MYAXA_PublicApps.war,WEB-INF/web.xml

This step is for advanced users and should only be used in those cases when all the runtime components needed for the application cannot be obtained by inspecting the application.

LR_MYAXA_Token_war&&MetadataCompleteForModules: Set the metadata-complete attribute of the deployment descriptor for the module
LR_MYAXA_Token_war&&The metadata-complete attribute defines whether the deployment descriptor for this module is complete. Set the metadata-complete attribute to "true" to merge and persist annotation-based metadata with existing XML-based deployment descriptor metedata to avoid scanning of annotation-based metadata each time the module is read. If the attribute remains "false", then the annotation-based metadata is scanned each time the module is read and can impact performance.

LR_PPRTG_VIDA_war&&MetadataCompleteForModules: Set the metadata-complete attribute of the deployment descriptor for the module
LR_PPRTG_VIDA_war&&The metadata-complete attribute defines whether the deployment descriptor for this module is complete. Set the metadata-complete attribute to "true" to merge and persist annotation-based metadata with existing XML-based deployment descriptor metedata to avoid scanning of annotation-based metadata each time the module is read. If the attribute remains "false", then the annotation-based metadata is scanned each time the module is read and can impact performance.

MPWebKYC&&
MPWebKYC&&MapRolesToUsers: Mapping users to roles
MPWebKYC&&Each role that is defined in the application or module must map to a user or group from the domain user registry.
MPWebKYC&&accessIds:
MPWebKYC&&	The accessIds are required only when using cross realm communication in a multi domain scenario. For all other scenarios the accessId will be determined during the application start based on the user or group name. The accessIds represent the user and group information that is used for Java Platform, Enterprise Edition authorization when using the WebSphere default authorization engine. The format for the accessIds is user:realm/uniqueUserID, group:realm/uniqueGroupID. Entering wrong information in these fields will cause authorization to fail.
MPWebKYC&&AllAuthenticatedInTrustedRealms:
MPWebKYC&&	This indicates that any valid user in the trusted realms be given the access.
MPWebKYC&&AllAuthenticated:
MPWebKYC&&	This indicates that any valid user in the current realm be given the access.
MPWebKYC&&Role:  MXAppBI_BUP_ROLC1
MPWebKYC&&Everyone?:  No
MPWebKYC&&All authenticated?:  No
MPWebKYC&&Mapped users:  
MPWebKYC&&Mapped groups:  MXAppBI_BUP_ROLC1

MPWeb_war&&MapJaspiProvider: Configure JASPI authentication.
MPWeb_war&&JASPI providers offer an alternative to JAAS pluggable authentication for web modules.  By default, an application inherits the JASPI settings defined in the WebSphere Application Server global or domain security configuration and web modules inherit the application setting.  However, you can override these defaults by using wsadmin or the administrative console.

MPWeb_war&&MapRolesToUsers: Mapping users to roles
MPWeb_war&&Each role that is defined in the application or module must map to a user or group from the domain user registry.
MPWeb_war&&accessIds:
MPWeb_war&&	The accessIds are required only when using cross realm communication in a multi domain scenario. For all other scenarios the accessId will be determined during the application start based on the user or group name. The accessIds represent the user and group information that is used for Java Platform, Enterprise Edition authorization when using the WebSphere default authorization engine. The format for the accessIds is user:realm/uniqueUserID, group:realm/uniqueGroupID. Entering wrong information in these fields will cause authorization to fail.
MPWeb_war&&AllAuthenticatedInTrustedRealms:
MPWeb_war&&	This indicates that any valid user in the trusted realms be given the access.
MPWeb_war&&AllAuthenticated:
MPWeb_war&&	This indicates that any valid user in the current realm be given the access.

MotorWorksiteDanos_war&&MapRolesToUsers: Mapping users to roles
MotorWorksiteDanos_war&&Each role that is defined in the application or module must map to a user or group from the domain user registry.
MotorWorksiteDanos_war&&accessIds:
MotorWorksiteDanos_war&&	The accessIds are required only when using cross realm communication in a multi domain scenario. For all other scenarios the accessId will be determined during the application start based on the user or group name. The accessIds represent the user and group information that is used for Java Platform, Enterprise Edition authorization when using the WebSphere default authorization engine. The format for the accessIds is user:realm/uniqueUserID, group:realm/uniqueGroupID. Entering wrong information in these fields will cause authorization to fail.
MotorWorksiteDanos_war&&AllAuthenticatedInTrustedRealms:
MotorWorksiteDanos_war&&	This indicates that any valid user in the trusted realms be given the access.
MotorWorksiteDanos_war&&AllAuthenticated:
MotorWorksiteDanos_war&&	This indicates that any valid user in the current realm be given the access.

MotorWorksites_war&&Also, specify the Web servers as targets that serve as routers for requests to this application. 
MotorWorksites_war&&The plug-in configuration file (plugin-cfg.xml) for each Web server is generated, based on the applications that are routed through.

MotorWorksites_war&&URI:  MotorWorksites.war,WEB-INF/web.xml

MotorWorksites_war&&MapJaspiProvider: Configure JASPI authentication.
MotorWorksites_war&&JASPI providers offer an alternative to JAAS pluggable authentication for web modules.  By default, an application inherits the JASPI settings defined in the WebSphere Application Server global or domain security configuration and web modules inherit the application setting.  However, you can override these defaults by using wsadmin or the administrative console.

MotorWorksites_war&&
MotorWorksites_war&&MapRolesToUsers: Mapping users to roles
MotorWorksites_war&&Each role that is defined in the application or module must map to a user or group from the domain user registry.
MotorWorksites_war&&accessIds:
MotorWorksites_war&&	The accessIds are required only when using cross realm communication in a multi domain scenario. For all other scenarios the accessId will be determined during the application start based on the user or group name. The accessIds represent the user and group information that is used for Java Platform, Enterprise Edition authorization when using the WebSphere default authorization engine. The format for the accessIds is user:realm/uniqueUserID, group:realm/uniqueGroupID. Entering wrong information in these fields will cause authorization to fail.
MotorWorksites_war&&AllAuthenticatedInTrustedRealms:
MotorWorksites_war&&	This indicates that any valid user in the trusted realms be given the access.
MotorWorksites_war&&AllAuthenticated:
MotorWorksites_war&&	This indicates that any valid user in the current realm be given the access.

MyAxaService_war&&MetadataCompleteForModules: Set the metadata-complete attribute of the deployment descriptor for the module
MyAxaService_war&&The metadata-complete attribute defines whether the deployment descriptor for this module is complete. Set the metadata-complete attribute to "true" to merge and persist annotation-based metadata with existing XML-based deployment descriptor metedata to avoid scanning of annotation-based metadata each time the module is read. If the attribute remains "false", then the annotation-based metadata is scanned each time the module is read and can impact performance. 
MyAxaService_war&&Module:  MyAxaServices.war
MyAxaService_war&&URI:  MyAxaServices.war,WEB-INF/web.xml

If the attribute remains "false", then the annotation-based metadata is scanned each time the module is read and can impact performance.

NvoSegHogar&&MapRolesToUsers: Mapping users to roles
NvoSegHogar&&Each role that is defined in the application or module must map to a user or group from the domain user registry.
NvoSegHogar&&accessIds:
NvoSegHogar&&	The accessIds are required only when using cross realm communication in a multi domain scenario. For all other scenarios the accessId will be determined during the application start based on the user or group name. The accessIds represent the user and group information that is used for Java Platform, Enterprise Edition authorization when using the WebSphere default authorization engine. The format for the accessIds is user:realm/uniqueUserID, group:realm/uniqueGroupID. Entering wrong information in these fields will cause authorization to fail.
NvoSegHogar&&AllAuthenticatedInTrustedRealms:
NvoSegHogar&&	This indicates that any valid user in the trusted realms be given the access.
NvoSegHogar&&AllAuthenticated:
NvoSegHogar&&	This indicates that any valid user in the current realm be given the access.

NvoSegHogar&&Specify runtime components that should be added to or removed from the default runtime components that are needed to run this application.  This step is for advanced users and should only be used in those cases when all the runtime components needed for the application cannot be obtained by inspecting the application.

['NvoSegHogarWS#NvoSegHogarWS.war+WEB-INF/web.xml']
NvoSegHogarWS&&MapModulesToServers: Selecting servers
NvoSegHogarWS&&Specify targets such as application servers or clusters of application servers where you want to install the modules that are contained in your application. Modules can be installed on the same application server or dispersed among several application servers. 
NvoSegHogarWS&&Also, specify the Web servers as targets that serve as routers for requests to this application. 
NvoSegHogarWS&&The plug-in configuration file (plugin-cfg.xml) for each Web server is generated, based on the applications that are routed through.
NvoSegHogarWS&&Module:  HogarWS
NvoSegHogarWS&&URI:  NvoSegHogarWS.war,WEB-INF/web.xml
NvoSegHogarWS&&Server:  WebSphere:cell=AXACellQA,node=apacheNode02QA,server=apacheExt_QA2+WebSphere:cell=AXACellQA,node=apacheNode01QA,server=apacheExt_QA1+WebSphere:cell=AXACellQA,cluster=cluster09_QA
NvoSegHogarWS&&
NvoSegHogarWS&&MapJaspiProvider: Configure JASPI authentication.
NvoSegHogarWS&&JASPI providers offer an alternative to JAAS pluggable authentication for web modules.  By default, an application inherits the JASPI settings defined in the WebSphere Application Server global or domain security configuration and web modules inherit the application setting.  However, you can override these defaults by using wsadmin or the administrative console.
NvoSegHogarWS&&Module:  NvoSegHogarWS
NvoSegHogarWS&&URI:  META-INF/application.xml
NvoSegHogarWS&&Use JASPI:  Inherit
NvoSegHogarWS&&JASPI provider name:  
NvoSegHogarWS&&Module:  HogarWS
NvoSegHogarWS&&URI:  NvoSegHogarWS.war,WEB-INF/web.xml
NvoSegHogarWS&&Use JASPI:  Inherit
NvoSegHogarWS&&JASPI provider name:  
NvoSegHogarWS&&
NvoSegHogarWS&&MapRolesToUsers: Mapping users to roles
NvoSegHogarWS&&Each role that is defined in the application or module must map to a user or group from the domain user registry.
NvoSegHogarWS&&accessIds:
NvoSegHogarWS&&	The accessIds are required only when using cross realm communication in a multi domain scenario. For all other scenarios the accessId will be determined during the application start based on the user or group name. The accessIds represent the user and group information that is used for Java Platform, Enterprise Edition authorization when using the WebSphere default authorization engine. The format for the accessIds is user:realm/uniqueUserID, group:realm/uniqueGroupID. Entering wrong information in these fields will cause authorization to fail.
NvoSegHogarWS&&AllAuthenticatedInTrustedRealms:
NvoSegHogarWS&&	This indicates that any valid user in the trusted realms be given the access.
NvoSegHogarWS&&AllAuthenticated:
NvoSegHogarWS&&	This indicates that any valid user in the current realm be given the access.
NvoSegHogarWS&&Role:  MXAppS_SED_WSEmisionSecRole
NvoSegHogarWS&&Everyone?:  No
NvoSegHogarWS&&All authenticated?:  No
NvoSegHogarWS&&Mapped users:  
NvoSegHogarWS&&Mapped groups:  MXAppS_SED_WSEmisionSecRole
NvoSegHogarWS&&All authenticated in trusted realms?:  No
NvoSegHogarWS&&Mapped users access ids:  
NvoSegHogarWS&&Mapped groups access ids:  group:AXARealm/CN=MXAppS_SED_WSEmisionSecRole,OU=Groups,OU=Usuarios,OU=AXA Mexico,DC=ASEFITEST,DC=MEX

Pagos_2&&MetadataCompleteForModules: Set the metadata-complete attribute of the deployment descriptor for the module
Pagos_2&&The metadata-complete attribute defines whether the deployment descriptor for this module is complete. Set the metadata-complete attribute to "true" to merge and persist annotation-based metadata with existing XML-based deployment descriptor metedata to avoid scanning of annotation-based metadata each time the module is read. If the attribute remains "false", then the annotation-based metadata is scanned each time the module is read and can impact performance. 
Pagos_2&&Module:  Pagos
Pagos_2&&URI:  Pagos.war,WEB-INF/web.xml
Pagos_2&&metadata-complete attribute:  false

Pagos_war&&Specify asset or composition unit IDs as shared libraries that the application or individual modules reference. If an asset ID is specified, a composition unit is created from the asset.

Pagos_war&&
Pagos_war&&MetadataCompleteForModules: Set the metadata-complete attribute of the deployment descriptor for the module
Pagos_war&&The metadata-complete attribute defines whether the deployment descriptor for this module is complete. Set the metadata-complete attribute to "true" to merge and persist annotation-based metadata with existing XML-based deployment descriptor metedata to avoid scanning of annotation-based metadata each time the module is read. If the attribute remains "false", then the annotation-based metadata is scanned each time the module is read and can impact performance. 
Pagos_war&&Module:  Pagos
Pagos_war&&URI:  Pagos.war,WEB-INF/web.xml
Pagos_war&&metadata-complete attribute:  false
Pagos_war&&
Pagos_war&&CustomActivationPlan: Specify runtime provisioning components to be added or removed
Pagos_war&&Specify runtime components that should be added to or removed from the default runtime components that are needed to run this application.  This step is for advanced users and should only be used in those cases when all the runtime components needed for the application cannot be obtained by inspecting the application.

Polizas&&Use JASPI:  Inherit
Polizas&&JASPI provider name:  
Polizas&&
Polizas&&MapRolesToUsers: Mapping users to roles
Polizas&&Each role that is defined in the application or module must map to a user or group from the domain user registry.
Polizas&&accessIds:
Polizas&&	The accessIds are required only when using cross realm communication in a multi domain scenario. For all other scenarios the accessId will be determined during the application start based on the user or group name. The accessIds represent the user and group information that is used for Java Platform, Enterprise Edition authorization when using the WebSphere default authorization engine. The format for the accessIds is user:realm/uniqueUserID, group:realm/uniqueGroupID. Entering wrong information in these fields will cause authorization to fail.
Polizas&&AllAuthenticatedInTrustedRealms:
Polizas&&	This indicates that any valid user in the trusted realms be given the access.
Polizas&&AllAuthenticated:
Polizas&&	This indicates that any valid user in the current realm be given the access.
Polizas&&Role:  MXAppS_SClaims_WS_Claims
Polizas&&Everyone?:  No
Polizas&&All authenticated?:  No
Polizas&&Mapped users:  
Polizas&&Mapped groups:  MXAppS_SClaims_WS_Claims
Polizas&&All authenticated in trusted realms?:  No
Polizas&&Mapped users access ids:  
Polizas&&Mapped groups access ids:  group:AXARealm/CN=MXAppS_SClaims_WS_Claims,OU=Groups,OU=Usuarios,OU=AXA Mexico,DC=ASEFITEST,DC=MEX
Polizas&&

Polizas_2&&accessIds:
Polizas_2&&	The accessIds are required only when using cross realm communication in a multi domain scenario. For all other scenarios the accessId will be determined during the application start based on the user or group name. The accessIds represent the user and group information that is used for Java Platform, Enterprise Edition authorization when using the WebSphere default authorization engine. The format for the accessIds is user:realm/uniqueUserID, group:realm/uniqueGroupID. Entering wrong information in these fields will cause authorization to fail.

If an asset ID is specified, a composition unit is created from the asset.

PrestadoresAxaServices_war&&
PrestadoresAxaServices_war&&MetadataCompleteForModules: Set the metadata-complete attribute of the deployment descriptor for the module
PrestadoresAxaServices_war&&The metadata-complete attribute defines whether the deployment descriptor for this module is complete. Set the metadata-complete attribute to "true" to merge and persist annotation-based metadata with existing XML-based deployment descriptor metedata to avoid scanning of annotation-based metadata each time the module is read. If the attribute remains "false", then the annotation-based metadata is scanned each time the module is read and can impact performance. 
PrestadoresAxaServices_war&&Module:  PrestadoresAxaServices
PrestadoresAxaServices_war&&URI:  PrestadoresAxaServices.war,WEB-INF/web.xml
PrestadoresAxaServices_war&&metadata-complete attribute:  false

PrimaPagadaAxa&&Specify targets such as application servers or clusters of application servers where you want to install the modules that are contained in your application. Modules can be installed on the same application server or dispersed among several application servers. 
PrimaPagadaAxa&&Also, specify the Web servers as targets that serve as routers for requests to this application.

PrimaPagadaAxa&&MapJaspiProvider: Configure JASPI authentication.
PrimaPagadaAxa&&JASPI providers offer an alternative to JAAS pluggable authentication for web modules.  By default, an application inherits the JASPI settings defined in the WebSphere Application Server global or domain security configuration and web modules inherit the application setting.  However, you can override these defaults by using wsadmin or the administrative console.

PrimaPagadaAxa&&MapRolesToUsers: Mapping users to roles
PrimaPagadaAxa&&Each role that is defined in the application or module must map to a user or group from the domain user registry.
PrimaPagadaAxa&&accessIds:
PrimaPagadaAxa&&	The accessIds are required only when using cross realm communication in a multi domain scenario. For all other scenarios the accessId will be determined during the application start based on the user or group name. The accessIds represent the user and group information that is used for Java Platform, Enterprise Edition authorization when using the WebSphere default authorization engine. The format for the accessIds is user:realm/uniqueUserID, group:realm/uniqueGroupID. Entering wrong information in these fields will cause authorization to fail.
PrimaPagadaAxa&&AllAuthenticatedInTrustedRealms:
PrimaPagadaAxa&&	This indicates that any valid user in the trusted realms be given the access.
PrimaPagadaAxa&&AllAuthenticated:
PrimaPagadaAxa&&	This indicates that any valid user in the current realm be given the access.

ProveedorALRSWSpreprod&&MapRolesToUsers: Mapping users to roles
ProveedorALRSWSpreprod&&Each role that is defined in the application or module must map to a user or group from the domain user registry.
ProveedorALRSWSpreprod&&accessIds:
ProveedorALRSWSpreprod&&	The accessIds are required only when using cross realm communication in a multi domain scenario. For all other scenarios the accessId will be determined during the application start based on the user or group name. The accessIds represent the user and group information that is used for Java Platform, Enterprise Edition authorization when using the WebSphere default authorization engine. The format for the accessIds is user:realm/uniqueUserID, group:realm/uniqueGroupID. Entering wrong information in these fields will cause authorization to fail.
ProveedorALRSWSpreprod&&AllAuthenticatedInTrustedRealms:
ProveedorALRSWSpreprod&&	This indicates that any valid user in the trusted realms be given the access.
ProveedorALRSWSpreprod&&AllAuthenticated:
ProveedorALRSWSpreprod&&	This indicates that any valid user in the current realm be given the access.
ProveedorALRSWSpreprod&&Role:  MXAppS_ApoyosLegal_SecInternalRole

ProveedorALRSWSpreprod&&MetadataCompleteForModules: Set the metadata-complete attribute of the deployment descriptor for the module
ProveedorALRSWSpreprod&&The metadata-complete attribute defines whether the deployment descriptor for this module is complete. Set the metadata-complete attribute to "true" to merge and persist annotation-based metadata with existing XML-based deployment descriptor metedata to avoid scanning of annotation-based metadata each time the module is read. If the attribute remains "false", then the annotation-based metadata is scanned each time the module is read and can impact performance.

PublicAXA_MEX_SME_360-portlet_war&&MetadataCompleteForModules: Set the metadata-complete attribute of the deployment descriptor for the module
PublicAXA_MEX_SME_360-portlet_war&&The metadata-complete attribute defines whether the deployment descriptor for this module is complete. Set the metadata-complete attribute to "true" to merge and persist annotation-based metadata with existing XML-based deployment descriptor metedata to avoid scanning of annotation-based metadata each time the module is read. If the attribute remains "false", then the annotation-based metadata is scanned each time the module is read and can impact performance.

Reportes&&MapJaspiProvider: Configure JASPI authentication.
Reportes&&JASPI providers offer an alternative to JAAS pluggable authentication for web modules.  By default, an application inherits the JASPI settings defined in the WebSphere Application Server global or domain security configuration and web modules inherit the application setting.  However, you can override these defaults by using wsadmin or the administrative console.

Reportes&&MapRolesToUsers: Mapping users to roles
Reportes&&Each role that is defined in the application or module must map to a user or group from the domain user registry.
Reportes&&accessIds:
Reportes&&	The accessIds are required only when using cross realm communication in a multi domain scenario. For all other scenarios the accessId will be determined during the application start based on the user or group name. The accessIds represent the user and group information that is used for Java Platform, Enterprise Edition authorization when using the WebSphere default authorization engine. The format for the accessIds is user:realm/uniqueUserID, group:realm/uniqueGroupID. Entering wrong information in these fields will cause authorization to fail.
Reportes&&AllAuthenticatedInTrustedRealms:
Reportes&&	This indicates that any valid user in the trusted realms be given the access.
Reportes&&AllAuthenticated:
Reportes&&	This indicates that any valid user in the current realm be given the access.
